  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "It would be nice for the [Forms doc](https://facebook.github.io/react/docs/forms.html) to be more explicit about the fact that React's `onChange` supersedes, and should generally be used in place of, the DOM's built-in `onInput` event. People might be used to using `onInput` instead for text inputs and textareas, since, with the raw DOM, the change event for these controls doesn't fire until the control loses focus.\n",
